<div id="review_357618774" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/357618774" />
    <a title="Scott Hutchins" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/967450-scott-hutchins"><img alt="Scott Hutchins" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442608180p2/967450.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/357618774?book_show_action=true">Jun 28, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Scott Hutchins" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Scott Hutchins" href="/user/show/967450-scott-hutchins">Scott Hutchins</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/967450-scott-hutchins?shelf=desert-island-books">desert-island-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer357618774" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7672068597976855438">I love Baldwin&apos;s fiction, but this collection of essays blows me away. His nonfiction voice is compassionate, self-deprecating, and incredibly smart. There&apos;s something of the oldest brother in his tone (I mean that in a good way). How he could see into the American heart so clearly is a mystery and a triumph. &quot;Notes of a Native Son&quot; is the most anthologized, but my favorite is &quot;Stranger in the Village.&quot; It makes me wish I was half as fierce and good as Baldwin.</span>
  <span id="freeText7672068597976855438" style="display:none">I love Baldwin's fiction, but this collection of essays blows me away. His nonfiction voice is compassionate, self-deprecating, and incredibly smart. There's something of the oldest brother in his tone (I mean that in a good way). How he could see into the American heart so clearly is a mystery and a triumph. "Notes of a Native Son" is the most anthologized, but my favorite is "Stranger in the Village." It makes me wish I was half as fierce and good as Baldwin.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7672068597976855438" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


